claim: The Daily Telegraph was the first newspaper to report the investigation into Sam Allardyce, although live news on the BBC broke the story hours before.
premise_source_doc_sentence: The Telegraph has been the first newspaper to report on a number of notable news scoops , including the 2009 MP expenses scandal , which led to a number of high-profile political resignations and for which it was named 2009 British Newspaper of the Year , and its 2016 undercover investigation on the England football manager Sam Allardyce .
